&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Behavioural characteristics&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our organisational culture is very important to us so it is vital that the postholder espouses our complimentary values and behaviours.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our key expectations are:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-awareness&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adaptability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Openness&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Positivity with a real sense of being able to strive for the impossible&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generosity of spirit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to have fun&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job purpose &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The administrative tasks undertaken by the post-holder will support the compliance, regulatory and quality requirements of the organisation service to both PDS (Medical) Limited and FCMS (NW) Limited.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post-holder will work as an integral member of the Risk &amp; Quality Team based at Newfield House and working from home. The team comprises of the Head and Deputy Head of Service, Service Lead and work alongside two additional members of staff.&lt;/p&gt;
